  "text": "Demers, et al. [CITATION_1] presented a generational collector which does not move objects, hence appropriate for conservative garbage collection. They partition the heap logically (instead of physically separating between generations) by keeping a bit per object indicating whether it is young or old. We adopt this idea. However, their collector is not concurrent.",
